(Condo App Launcher Cloud Implementation Plan) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Goal: Build the Electron launcher architecture on AWS first while preserving) Tj
T*
(a clean path to Azure and Google Cloud.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Recommended implementation steps:) Tj
T*
(1. Document the launcher workflow and backend API contract.) Tj
T*
(2. Keep Docker as the packaging baseline with multi-architecture builds.) Tj
T*
(3. Launch an AWS-first backend with ECR, S3, API Gateway, Lambda, Cognito,) Tj
T*
(   and DynamoDB.) Tj
T*
(4. Add CloudWatch logging, alarms, and Secrets Manager-based secret storage.) Tj
T*
(5. Create CI/CD pipelines for Docker images and Electron installers.) Tj
T*
(6. Introduce queued remote operations such as restart, diagnostics, and) Tj
T*
(   shutdown.) Tj
T*
(7. Abstract infrastructure with Terraform modules for Azure and Google Cloud.) Tj
T*
(8. Adopt managed databases and provider-native automation as requirements grow.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Cloud service mapping:) Tj
T*
(- Registry: ECR / Azure Container Registry / Artifact Registry) Tj
T*
(- Serverless API: API Gateway + Lambda / API Management + Azure Functions /) Tj
T*
(  API Gateway + Cloud Functions) Tj
T*
(- Container runtime: ECS Fargate / Azure Container Apps / Cloud Run) Tj
T*
(- Identity: Cognito / Microsoft Entra External ID / Identity Platform) Tj
T*
(- NoSQL state store: DynamoDB / Cosmos DB / Firestore) Tj
T*
(- Queue/eventing: SQS + EventBridge / Service Bus + Event Grid /) Tj
T*
(  Pub/Sub + Eventarc) Tj
T*
(- Secrets: Secrets Manager / Key Vault / Secret Manager) Tj
T*
(- Observability: CloudWatch / Azure Monitor / Cloud Logging) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Delivery phases:) Tj
T*
(- Phase 1: local orchestration plus cloud auth, config, and updates.) Tj
T*
(- Phase 2: remote callable actions, machine registration, and diagnostics.) Tj
T*
(- Phase 3: managed databases, scheduled maintenance, and tenant automation.) Tj
T*
(- Phase 4: multi-region resilience and optional multi-cloud failover.) Tj
